    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - LIGHT SYSTEMS - TROUBLESHOOTING</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <seqlist style="alphauc">
                <item>
                    <para>Before beginning these test procedures, make sure the vehicle batteries are at 75% state of
                        charge (SOC) or higher. This represents an open circuit voltage (OCV) of 12.4 volts. Batteries
                        with an OCV of 12 volts or less are either completely discharged or have a dead cell.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Before beginning these test procedures, check any light or indicator lamp filaments that are
                        suspected of being open (burned out). This is done to avoid unnecessary extensive circuit
                        checks.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Before beginning these test procedures, inspect all connectors for loose or damaged pins,
                        wires, etc. Refer to TEST EQUIPMENT AND CONNECTOR REPAIR section in GROUP 08 - ELECTRICAL in the
                        CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>When the technician determines that a fuse is blown, while checking its condition, he is
                        directed to locate the cause of the overload condition and to repair it. While no further
                        instruction on this procedure is listed in the diagnostic tables, the common procedure is as
                        follows: isolate sections of the circuit by disconnecting connectors, and measure the resistance
                        to ground to find the circuit that is shorted to ground. Then locate the damaged spot in the
                        wire or connector and repair.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Diagnostics for circuits that are malfunctioning by sticking in the on position are generally
                        not covered in detail. It is assumed that the technician knows to check for a malfunctioning
                        switch, relay, or solenoid.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Back-Up Lights</title>
            <table id="t0824001" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Back-Up Lights</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.57in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.78in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.69in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.53in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Check fuse F1</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>F1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At F1 measure voltage from 13 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>F1, 13 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 13, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove conn. (2). Turn key on and measure voltage at (2) circuit 71 to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(2), 71 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 71, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Reconnect conn. (2) and remove conn. from back-up light switch (317) or (375), or
                                    relay conn. (304).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure voltage from feed circuit (71 or 313CM or black wire) to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Feed circuit to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in feed circuit, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Does vehicle have an electronically controlled Allison automatic transmission?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to Step 8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With transmission in reverse, measure resistance across terminals of back-up light
                                    switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Back up light switch across term.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to Step 9.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace defective switch and reconnect connector.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With key switch in ignition position and automatic transmission in reverse,
                                    measure voltage between Pin A and B of conn. (304).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(304), pin A to B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate problem with Vehicle Interface Module or wiring, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>9.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With all other connectors reconnected, disconnect conn. (13) and move key switch
                                    (24) to ignition position. Measure voltage from circuit 71A to ground with
                                    transmission in reverse.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(13), 71A to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuits 71A and 71B, or connector (2), then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>10.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Reconnect (13) and disconnect (700/701). Turn key on and measure voltage from blue
                                    wire to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(700/ 701), blue wire to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in blue wire, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>11.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With transmission still in reverse, measure voltage from blue wire to white wire
                                    at conn. (700/701).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(700/ 701), blue to white wire.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in ground circuit (white wire), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>12.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Back-up light circuits check good. Replace any defective backup lights.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcproc>
